  "text": "The murine macrophage cell line RAW 264.7 was purchased from ATCC (Manassas, VA). RAW 264.7 cells were maintained in RPMI supplemented with 5% FBS and antibiotic-antimycotic (1000 U/ml penicillin, 1000 mg/ml streptomycin sulfate, and 250 ng/ml amphotericin B) at 37uC. Mouse embryonic fibroblasts (MEFs) cell line lacking specific NFkB signaling subunits NF-kB p65 (p652/2 cell line) [CITATION_1] were cultured in DMEM medium supplemented with 10% FBS and antibiotic-antimycotic solution.",
